- Approved equivalencies mean that the courses have been recognized and accepted by the institution;
- Active program policies indicate that the policies governing the transfer of credits are in effect on the specified date;
- The Fall 2023 semester is a specific academic term during the 2023-2024 academic year.

- 'blossoming programs' refers to programs with a high number of course offerings;
- 'flowers of knowledge bloom abundantly' refers to programs with a high number of offerings in both the Spring and Fall semesters;
- 'top quartile' means the top 25% when ranked by the total number of course offerings.

- "blossomed with more than 6 credit hours" refers to programs requiring more than 6 credit hours;
